./.title: Installing
./.body:
Requirements
In order to use this library you'll need

nodeJS > v6.x.x
A twitch token that you can get by connecting here : http://twitchapps.com/tmi/
The ID of your account that you can get through the API
Having your account being moderator on the channel you want to listen events on
basic JS knowledge

Installation
Create a directory for you project, go to it in your command line. Then use npm to install the lib by typing :  
npm i twitch-moderation-pubsub --save
Support
In case you ever need help you can join the Discord Server related to the library.
Links
Github : https://github.com/Equinoxbig/twitch-moderation-pubsub
npm : https://www.npmjs.com/package/twitch-moderation-pubsub

addTopic.html.title: addTopic
addTopic.html.body:
Description
Used to listen to a new topic.
Example
// ... Initializing

pubsub.addTopic('41677043')
    .then(console.log)
    .catch(console.error);

Parameters
topic - {String} - The ID of a twitch channel as a string.
Returns
{
    topic: '41677043',
    err: 'success',
    shard: Shard
}


topic - {String} - The topic given as parameter.
err - {String} - The error message, 'success' if the request succeed.
shard - {Shard} - The Shard object to which the topic has been added.
